President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Michael A. Hammer as Assistant Secretary for Public Affairs at the Department of State and Charles McConnell as Assistant Secretary for Fossil Energy at the Department of Energy. He also intends to appoint Terry Guen, Dorothy T. Lippert, and Rosemary A. Joyce to key advisory council and committee positions. Hammer is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and currently serves as the Acting Assistant Secretary and Principal Deputy Assistant Secretary for Public Affairs at the State Department. McConnell is the Chief Operating Officer in the Office of Fossil Energy at the Department of Energy. Guen is the president and principal of a Chicago-based consultancy specializing in landscape architecture. Lippert is a Case Officer at the National Museum of Natural History at the Smithsonian Institution. Joyce is a professor of anthropology and an expert on Honduran archaeology.